On January 9, Biden announced the allocation of $500 million in military aid to Ukraine under the PDA program.
From the available reserves of the US Army will be transferred:
AIM-7 Sparrow, RIM-7 Sea Sparrow and AIM-9M Sidewinder missiles for the FrankenSAM family of air defense systems;
Unnamed air-to-ground ammunition;
Auxiliary equipment for F-16 fighter jets;
Armored bridge-laying machines;
Secure means of communication;
Small arms and ammunition;
Spare parts, auxiliary equipment, as well as training and transportation services.
